    <h3 itemprop="headline">The Supreme Court rules for Biden administration in a social media dispute with conservative states</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      WASHINGTON (AP) — The Supreme Court on Wednesday sided with the Biden administration in a dispute with Republican-led states over how far the federal government can go to combat controversial social media posts on topics including COVID-19 and election security.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/06/27/the-supreme-court-rules-for-biden-administration-in-a-social-media-dispute-with-conservative-states/"  >(MARK SHERMAN, Associated Press, ABC 4)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
